
   #  Strongly typed
      +  Python is strongly typed #16
   #  Objects
      +  All data type in Python are created as Objects #15
      +  This includes : numbers, strings, tuples & functions etc... #93
      
   #  'type'   #17
      +  Can be used to identify the type of a variable or literal value
      >>> a = 7
      >>> type(a)
      <class 'int'>
      >>> type(9)
      <class 'int'>
      >>> type('a')
      <class 'str'>
      
   #  Variable name constraints 
      +  Python treats variables starting with '_' in a special way #18
      +  Reserved keywords 
         .  Check here for more...#19
         
   #  Division #22
      +  Decimal division     : uses '/'
      +  Truncating division  : uses '//'
      +  Reminder             : uses '%'
      +  divmod()             : Provides Quotient and reminder Tuple #23
      >>> 8/5
      1.6
      >>> 8//5
      1       
      >>> divmod(8,5)
      (1, 3)
      
         
         
         
         
         
         
               

      
                     